<p>Weborf is a lightweight webserver designed to rapidly share directories. Runs on GNU/Linux systems and is meant to solve <a href="http://xkcd.com/949/">this problem</a>.</p>

<p>It comes with a GUI called <a href="qweborf.html">qweborf</a> to make it easier to know the IP address, traverse the NAT, use authentication.</p>

<img src="images/file_transfer.png">

<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Qt GUI or and command line</li>
    <li>Webdav support</li>
    <li>Cache to speed up webdav operations</li>
    <li>SSL support</li>
    <li>(x)inetd support</li>
    <li>Compress directories on the fly</li>
    <li>CGI support</li>
    <li>systemd integration</li>
</ul>
